==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ferro-concrete
<hw>Fer"ro-con"crete</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Arch. &
Engin.)</fld> <def>Concrete strengthened by a core or foundation
skeleton of iron or steel bars, strips, etc. Floors, columns, piles,
water pipes, etc., have been successfully made of it. Called also
<altname>armored concrete steel</altname>, and most commonly
<altname>reenforced concrete</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ferrocyanate</ent>⟦br⟧
